{"id":1235374076,"question_id":463,"lang":"java","lang_name":"Java","time":"1 month, 1 week","timestamp":1713408949,"status":10,"status_display":"Accepted","runtime":"4 ms","url":"/submissions/detail/1235374076/","is_pending":"Not Pending","title":"Island Perimeter","memory":"45.6 MB","code":"class Solution {\n    public int islandPerimeter(int[][] grid) {\n        int perimeter = 0;\n        int rows = grid.length;\n        int cols = grid[0].length;\n        \n        // Iterate through the grid\n        for (int i = 0; i < rows; i++) {\n            for (int j = 0; j < cols; j++) {\n                // Check if current cell is land\n                if (grid[i][j] == 1) {\n                    // Check top neighbor\n                    if (i == 0 || grid[i - 1][j] == 0) {\n                        perimeter++;\n                    }\n                    // Check bottom neighbor\n                    if (i == rows - 1 || grid[i + 1][j] == 0) {\n                        perimeter++;\n                    }\n                    // Check left neighbor\n                    if (j == 0 || grid[i][j - 1] == 0) {\n                        perimeter++;\n                    }\n                    // Check right neighbor\n                    if (j == cols - 1 || grid[i][j + 1] == 0) {\n                        perimeter++;\n                    }\n                }\n            }\n        }\n        \n        return perimeter;\n    }\n}\n","compare_result":"","title_slug":"island-perimeter","has_notes":false,"flag_type":1}
